The Council of Economic Advisers has released its seventh quarterly report on the economic impact of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act. The report states that the Recovery Act has played a significant role in supporting the economy, adding as much as 3.2 percent to the level of first quarter GDP and creating as many as 3.6 million jobs. GDP has been steadily growing for seven consecutive quarters, and the Recovery Act has raised the level of GDP by 2.3 to 3.2 percent as of the first quarter of 2011. Overall, the Recovery Act has contributed to the turnaround of the economy, with the addition of 2.1 million private sector jobs over the past 15 months.